title: Grateful Dead Live at Manor Downs on 1981-07-04
lineage: MAC > Nakamichi CR-5A > Edirol FA-66 > Wavelab 2448 > CD-Wave (24bit output) > R8Brain > TLH > FLAC 1644 tagged. Transferred by Andrew F. 09/2015
description:
Set 1

Jack Straw, Peggy-O, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Loser, Little Red Rooster, Tennessee Jed-> Minglewood Blues, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider

Set 2

Feel Like A Stranger, Bird Song-> Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Wharf Rat-> Sugar Magnolia, E: One More Saturday Night

reviews.review_text:
sang a little tune and then flew off That's a perfect looking second set on a paper and it sounds pretty great on this recording, too.

Stranger has a relatively mellow groove but will "get you there" unless you have an aversion to Brent's snakey keyboard lines (I love 'em).

Another fine Peggy O in set one.  If that had showed up later in the set -- just prior to China Cat, maybe -- it'd be like some sort of dreamed up setlist that could never really happen (and it didn't).

This will do just fine, however.
Best sound, great show. I prefer this aud to all other sources, including sbd's.   Great performance too.
